#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:5
msgid "fish_indent - indenter and prettifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:8
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:10
msgid "fish_indent [OPTIONS] [FILE ...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:16
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:18
msgid ""
":program:`fish_indent` is used to indent a piece of fish code. :program:"
"`fish_indent` reads commands from standard input or the given filenames and "
"outputs them to standard output or a specified file (if ``-w`` is given)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:20
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:22
msgid "**-w** or **--write**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:23
msgid "Indents a specified file and immediately writes to that file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:25
msgid "**-i** or **--no-indent**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:26
msgid "Do not indent commands; only reformat to one job per line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:28
msgid "**-c** or **--check**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:29
msgid ""
"Do not indent, only return 0 if the code is already indented as fish_indent "
"would, the number of failed files otherwise. Also print the failed filenames "
"if not reading from standard input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:31
msgid "**-v** or **--version**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:32
msgid "Displays the current :program:`fish` version and then exits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:34
msgid "**--ansi**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:35
msgid ""
"Colorizes the output using ANSI escape sequences, appropriate for the "
"current :envvar:`TERM`, using the colors defined in the environment (such "
"as :envvar:`fish_color_command`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:37
msgid "**--html**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:38
msgid ""
"Outputs HTML, which supports syntax highlighting if the appropriate CSS is "
"defined. The CSS class names are the same as the variable names, such as "
"``fish_color_command``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:40
msgid "**-d** or **--debug=DEBUG_CATEGORIES**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:41
msgid ""
"Enable debug output and specify a pattern for matching debug categories. "
"See :ref:`Debugging <debugging-fish>` in :doc:`fish <fish>` (1) for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:43
msgid "**-o** or **--debug-output=DEBUG_FILE**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:44
msgid ""
"Specify a file path to receive the debug output, including categories and "
"``fish_trace``. The default is standard error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:46
msgid "**--dump-parse-tree**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:47
msgid ""
"Dumps information about the parsed statements to standard error. This is "
"likely to be of interest only to people working on the fish source code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:49
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_indent.rst:50
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""
